quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  89,1,"By the dawn"
  89,2,"And [by] ten nights{1}",footnotes:1:1
  89,3,"And [by] the even [number] and the odd"
  89,4,"And [by] the night when it passes,"
  89,5,"Is there [not] in [all] that an oath [sufficient] for one of perception?{1}",footnotes:1:1
  89,6,"Have you not considered how your Lord dealt with ʿAad -"
  89,7,"[With] Iram{1} - who had lofty pillars,{2}",footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  89,8,"The likes of whom had never been created in the land?"
  89,9,"And [with] Thamūd, who carved out the rocks in the valley?"
  89,10,"And [with] Pharaoh, owner of the stakes?{1}",footnotes:1:1